Does this atomic increment in a tight loop cause severe false sharing
and cache-line contention?

Since all 16 threads continuously update the shared verified atomic variable
in this loop, the cache line ping-pong might significantly bottleneck reader
throughput.

As the test relies on high reader throughput to hit a timing-sensitive
race condition, could we use thread-local counters instead and only
aggregate them after the loop?

