Can this signal handler deadlock?

The thp_restore_settings() function eventually calls non-async-signal-safe
libc functions like snprintf() and printf() via thp_write_string().

If the test process receives SIGINT or SIGTERM while it is already
executing a libc function, attempting to re-acquire the internal libc
mutexes could cause the test suite to hang.

